courses.subject: GE
courses.customDesc: One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, C1, C2, Lower-Division C Elective, Upper-Division C, D1, D2, Upper-Division D, F, and GE Elective. Upper-Division C and Upper-Division D should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). Refer to online catalog for GE course selection and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR).

courses.subject: Choose One
courses.customDesc:
Choose one of the following: CHEM312, or CHEM216.

Most Nutrition majors should take CHEM312 and CHEM314. Students choosing the Nutrition Science concentration may need to take CHEM216 and CHEM369, depending on their career goals and approved electives. Students selecting CHEM216 must also take CHEM217 and CHEM218. See advisor.
